Bahrain Islamic and Gulf Finance House: Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-06-02T02:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/bahrain-islamic-and-gulf-finance-house-gulf-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in Persian Gulf markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
prices are from the last close.  Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  rose 0.9 percent to the highest
level since May 22 and  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  gained 1
percent. Saudi Arabia’s market is closed for the weekend.    Bahrain Islamic Bank (BISB)  BSC: The Bahraini Islamic
lender had its credit ratings cut to junk at Moody’s Investors
Service because of losses and after political unrest in the
Persian Gulf nation. The shares jumped 1.9 percent to 0.106
dinar when they last traded May 31.       Gulf Finance House BSC (GFH BI): The Bahrain-based
investment bank will resume trading after a capital increase and
a so-called reverse stock split. The shares last traded on Oct.
12 and were unchanged at 50 cents.    Qatar International Islamic Bank (QIIK)  : The country’s
third-largest Islamic bank by assets had a first-time ratings
assignment of A3/Prime-2 at Moody’s. The shares advanced 0.8
percent to 46.6 riyals.  Editors:  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
